🔧 C Programming Operators


1️⃣ Arithmetic Operators ➕➖✖️➗
📌 Used for basic mathematical operations.

Operator	  Description         	Example
+	           Addition           	a + b
-	           Subtraction	        a - b
*	           Multiplication	      a * b
/	           Division	            a / b
%	          Modulus (Remainder)	  a % b


🧪 Example:

int a = 10, b = 3;
int sum = a + b;        // 13
int diff = a - b;       // 7
int prod = a * b;       // 30
int quot = a / b;       // 3
int rem = a % b;        // 1



2️⃣ Relational Operators 🔁
📌 Used to compare values. Results in true (1) or false (0).

Operator	   Meaning	                 Example
==	         Equal to                 	x == y
!=	         Not equal to	              x != y
>	         Greater than	              x > y
<	         Less than	                  x < y
>=	         Greater than or equal     	x >= y
<=	         Less than or equal	        x <= y


🧪 Example:

int x = 5, y = 10;
if (x < y) {
    // True: Executes this block
}


3️⃣ Logical Operators 🧠
📌 Combine or invert boolean expressions.

Operator        	Name         	Example
&&	              Logical AND	     x > 0 && y > 0
!	              Logical NOT	     !(x > y)


🧪 Example:
if (x > 0 && y > 0) {
    // Both positive
}



4️⃣ Bitwise Operators ⚙️
📌 Operate on bits directly — used in low-level programming.

Operator        	Operation	     Example
&	               Bitwise AND	    a & b
`		           Bitwise OR
^	               Bitwise XOR	    a ^ b
~	               Bitwise NOT      ~a
<<	               Left shift      	a << 1
>>	               Right shift     	a >> 1


🧪 Example:

int a = 5, b = 3;
// Binary: 0101 & 0011 = 0001
int result = a & b; // 1



5️⃣ Assignment Operators 📝
📌 Assign and modify values in one step.

Operator         	Description           	Equivalent To
=	                 Assignment	             x = 5
+=	               Add and assign         	x = x + 5
-=	               Subtract and assign     	x = x - 5
*=	               Multiply and assign	    x = x * 5
/=	               Divide and assign       	x = x / 5
%=	               Modulo and assign	      x = x % 5


🧪 Example:
int x = 10;
x += 5; // x becomes 15


6️⃣ Unary Operators ☝️
📌 Work with a single operand.

Operator	   Meaning
++	         Increment
--	         Decrement
+	           Unary Plus
-	           Unary Minus


🧪 Example:

int value = 5;
value++;   // 6
--value;   // back to 5



7️⃣ Ternary Operator ❔
📌 Shortcut for if-else.
🔹 Syntax: condition ? true_expr : false_expr;
🧪 Example:
int a = 10, b = 20;
int max = (a > b) ? a : b; // max = 20



8️⃣ Sizeof Operator 📏
📌 Returns memory size of a variable/type in bytes.
🧪 Example:
int x;
printf("Size of int: %zu bytes\n", sizeof(x));


9️⃣ Comma Operator 🧮
📌 Used to evaluate multiple expressions in a single statement.
🧪 Example:
int x = (1, 2, 3); // x = 3 (last value)


🔟 Member Access Operators 🧷
📌 Used to access members of structures/unions.
Operator	Description	Usage
.	Access using object	object.member
->	Access using pointer to object	ptr->member

🧪 Example:

struct Point { int x; int y; };
struct Point p1 = {10, 20};
printf("%d\n", p1.x);       // Dot
struct Point *ptr = &p1;
printf("%d\n", ptr->y);     // Arrow
